00793 // Mutifunctional method to get and set values to a collection
00794 // The value/s can be optionally by executed if its a function
00795 function access( elems, key, value, exec, fn, pass ) {
00796       var length = elems.length;
00797       
00798       // Setting many attributes
00799       if ( typeof key === "object" ) {
00800             for ( var k in key ) {
00801                   access( elems, k, key[k], exec, fn, value );
00802             }
00803             return elems;
00804       }
00805       
00806       // Setting one attribute
00807       if ( value !== undefined ) {
00808             // Optionally, function values get executed if exec is true
00809             exec = !pass && exec && jQuery.isFunction(value);
00810             
00811             for ( var i = 0; i < length; i++ ) {
00812                   fn( elems[i], key, exec ? value.call( elems[i], i, fn( elems[i], key ) ) : value, pass );
00813             }
00814             
00815             return elems;
00816       }
00817       
00818       // Getting an attribute
00819       return length ? fn( elems[0], key ) : undefined;
00820 }

04352 function buildFragment( args, nodes, scripts ) {
04353       var fragment, cacheable, cacheresults,
04354             doc = (nodes && nodes[0] ? nodes[0].ownerDocument || nodes[0] : document);
04355 
04356       // Only cache "small" (1/2 KB) strings that are associated with the main document
04357       // Cloning options loses the selected state, so don't cache them
04358       // IE 6 doesn't like it when you put <object> or <embed> elements in a fragment
04359       // Also, WebKit does not clone 'checked' attributes on cloneNode, so don't cache
04360       if ( args.length === 1 && typeof args[0] === "string" && args[0].length < 512 && doc === document &&
04361             !rnocache.test( args[0] ) && (jQuery.support.checkClone || !rchecked.test( args[0] )) ) {
04362

04364             cacheresults = jQuery.fragments[ args[0] ];

04366                   if ( cacheresults !== 1 ) {
04367                         fragment = cacheresults;
04368                   }
04369             }
04370       }
04371 
04372       if ( !fragment ) {
04373             fragment = doc.createDocumentFragment();

04375       }
04376 
04377       if ( cacheable ) {
04378             jQuery.fragments[ args[0] ] = cacheresults ? fragment : 1;
04379       }
